FT  12 AUG 92 / Kabul claims rout of rebels
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Afghan government forces claimed victory yesterday after two days of fierce
fighting with a dissident mujahideen group, saying the dissidents had been
routed from positions south of the capital Kabul, Reuter reports from
Islamabad.
'The Islamic army crushed their attacks, and pushed back the enemy from
their positions,' the Defence Ministry said on state-run Kabul Radio.
The hardline Hezb-i-Islami group said fighting was still going on around
Kabul and offered conditions to end their bombardment of the city that has
left more than 1,000 dead or injured.
