<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 92 / French dockers step up action
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The threat of a summer of discontent looms in France with dockers calling a
nation-wide dock strike today and disgruntled farmers renewing protests
against EC agricultural reforms, Alice Rawsthorn reports from Paris.
The dock strike will be the second national stoppage at France's ports this
week.
Farmers yesterday occupied the Agriculture Ministry's office at Auch in the
Gers region seeking the right to put their case to Mr Pierre Beregovoy,
French prime minister.
</TEXT>
