FT  12 AUG 92 / International Company News: Dismay at store appointment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE appointment of Mr Arthur Martinez to head the troubled retail division
of Sears, Roebuck, has left noses badly out of joint at P. A. Bergner, the
bankrupt Milwaukee-based retail group, writes Nikki Tait.
The company said yesterday it had been negotiating for several months to
secure Mr Martinez's services as chief executive - and had filed a motion
with the bankruptcy court to approve an employment contract.
Yesterday, Mr Bertrand Maus, Bergner's chairman was quoted as saying he was
'personally shocked and angry that with virtually no notice to us, he (Mr
Martinez) has chosen to join Sears, Roebuck'.
Mr Martinez, previously a senior executive with Saks Fifth Avenue, is due to
join Sears on September 1.
