<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 92 / International Company News: USX offers 7.5m shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
USX, the US steel and energy group, yesterday said it had filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission to offer 7.5m shares in a new class of
USX common stock to be called USX-Delhi Group common stock. The initial
public offering price will be between Dollars 16 and Dollars 18 a share,
according to the company's registration statement.
USX said in April it might sell shares in its Delhi Group, including the
Delhi gas pipe line and other related companies, as part of its efforts to
realise shareholder value. The Delhi Group had sales of over Dollars 423m in
1991, with operating income of about Dollars 31m and assets of Dollars 598m.
USX had also considered selling assets or creating a limited partnership.
USX said yesterday the proceeds from the offering would be used for the
business purposes of its Marathon gas group. The Delhi group had been part
of the Marathon group.
The effort to realise additional value for Marathon follows the company's
stock split last year, when USX agreed to issue a new class of stock after
pressure from Mr Carl Icahn, the New York financier.
