<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CALTEX Australia, the Sydney-based petroleum group, has returned to the
black in the first half to June, helped by a big asset sale.
However, the company yesterday announced a heavy restructuring programme
which will cut the workforce by almost 14 per cent.
The company turned after-tax losses of ADollars 18.4m (USDollars 13.6m) into
ADollars 7.9m profits on a 2.5 per cent rise in sales to ADollars 1.64bn
