FT  12 AUG 92 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
If you have been out of the country for a few years, tonight provides a
chance to catch up on what you missed on television. BBC1 shows a repeat
episode of Lovejoy (8.00), the series about a canny antique dealer. BBC2
repeats an episode of Rough Guide To Careers (7.30) covering money jobs:
accountant, croupier, and so on. It also repeats the 'ScreenPlay' drama
