<TEXT>
Sir, I refer to Mr Onesimo Alvarez-Moro's letter (August 7) and his advice
for Italians to wake up as soon as possible - I would like to know when the
Spaniards woke up, if they did.
The Spanish unemployment rate is at 17 per cent of the workforce; inflation
will touch 7 per cent average rate in 1992 and only the government believes
that the economic growth will be more than 2 per cent. Real economic
indicators show the same results. In fact the Spanish government begged for
special help at Maastricht, called the cohesion fund.
Concerning the old tricks, I would advise Mr Alvarez-Moro to read the
Spanish newspapers of the last months.
Three or four years of good results, boosted by foreign investments, are
nothing in the history of a company, even less in the history of a country.
