FT  11 AUG 92 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was strong and active demand with 14,660 packages for the day reports
the Tea Brokers' Association. Landed brightest East African teas and the
better liquoring mediums showed further gains. Plainer mediums were a strong
feature and often 5 to 10p dearer. Central African teas met fair
competition. Ceylons attracted fair support at about last levels except the
plainer teas which were often neglected. Offshore good demand with prices
firm on last rates. The highest price realised this week was 205p for a
Rwanda pf. 1. Quotations: quality 170, nom good medium 140p, medium 125p,
low medium 80p.
