It announced a 6 per cent rise in earnings to ADollars 48.3m (USDollars
35.7m) for the year to May. A final dividend of 18 cents a share has been
declared, making an unchanged 35 cents for the year.
Non-performing loans stood at ADollars 60m and loans under management at
ADollars 112m.
