<HEADLINE>
FT  11 AUG 92 / UK Company News: New Ireland static at IPounds 2.63m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
New Ireland Holdings, the Dublin-based composite insurance company
ultimately controlled by UAP, a French insurance group, reported a static
first six months with pre-tax profits of IPounds 2.63m (Pounds 2.47m),
against IPounds 2.65m.
Earnings per share were 9.6p (10.4p). An unchanged interim dividend of 3.3p
is declared.
The pre-tax profit included IPounds 1.53m (IPounds 1.32m) from general
insurance but a lower IPounds 884,000 (IPounds 1.13m) return on investments.
