FT  11 AUG 92 / Sri Lankans stone ministers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COLOMBO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Thousands of mourners hurled stones and abuse at Sri Lankan government
ministers at the funeral yesterday of a popular general killed in a weekend
landmine explosion, Reuter reports from Colombo.
At least 15 people, including two ministers and some soldiers, were injured.
Police in riot gear fired shots and tear-gas into the air to disperse the
crowd of more than 100,000 surrounding top military men and politicians at
the Colombo funeral.
Denzil Kobbekaduwa, posthumously promoted to lieutenant-general from
major-general, was killed with nine other people in the blast in northern
Jaffna on Saturday.
